+        <strong>Without structured concurrency (tokio, async-std):</strong>
+        <code style="color:var(--cyan);">tokio::spawn()</code> returns a detached <code>JoinHandle</code>. If you drop it, the task becomes an orphan — running indefinitely, holding resources, invisible to the parent scope. There is no "close region and wait for children" primitive. You must manually track every spawned task and <code>.await</code> each <code>JoinHandle</code>. Miss one? Zombie task. Forever.
