+      <div class="callout-contrast callout-danger mt-2">
+        <strong>Without cascade close (tokio, Node.js):</strong>
+        You must manually track every spawned task, every open connection, every pending timer, and ensure each one is cleaned up in every error path. Close the HTTP handler but forget the database connections it spawned? Leaked. Close the connection pool but forget a query mid-flight? Leaked. With N components, you have O(N&sup2;) cleanup coordination points. Asupersync: <code style="color:var(--cyan);">scope.close()</code> — one call, guaranteed.
+      </div>
